[0m[49m[39m  157, 152[0m:[39m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[39m  158, 153[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  159, 154[0m:[39m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[39m  160, 155[0m:[39m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 161     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **AWS Services** | Lambda, S3, ECS (Fargate), DynamoDB, EventBridge, SageMaker, QuickSight |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 162     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `lambda:InvokeFunction`, `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `ecs:RunTask`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:Query`, `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint`, `events:PutRule` |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 163     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **BAA** | Required if scheduling data includes patient identifiers (it typically does: surgeon names, case types by patient) |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 164     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest; ECS: encrypt task storage; all transit over TLS |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 165     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **VPC** | Production: Fargate tasks and Lambda in VPC with VPC endpoints for S3, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 166     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled: log all optimization runs and schedule modifications for audit trail |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 167     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Solver License** | If using Gurobi/CPLEX: cloud license (token server or machine ID based). If using open-source (HiGHS, CBC): no license needed. |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 168     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Sample Data** | Synthetic OR utilization data. Use realistic distributions: 60-85% utilization, 5-15% cancellation rate, 10-50 rooms. Never use actual patient/surgeon identifiers in dev. |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 169     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | SageMaker inference: ~$5-20/month for weekly forecasts. Fargate solver tasks: ~$0.50-5 per solve (depends on problem size and duration). Lambda, DynamoDB, S3: negligible. Total: $50-200/month for weekly batch optimization. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon SageMaker, Amazon S3, AWS Lambda, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon QuickSight, AWS Step Functions, Amazon EventBridge, Amazon SNS |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `sagemaker:CreateProcessingJob`, `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:Query`, `lambda:InvokeFunction`, `states:StartExecution` |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **BAA** | Required if optimization inputs include patient identifiers. Block scheduling typically uses aggregated service-level data (not PHI), but if you're including surgeon names or patient wait lists, sign the BAA. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest (default); Lambda environment variables: KMS encrypted |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **VPC** | Production: SageMaker Processing in VPC with VPC endpoints for S3 and DynamoDB. Lambda in VPC if accessing EHR integration endpoints. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled: log all S3 and DynamoDB API calls. Allocation changes are auditable decisions. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Sample Data** | Synthetic OR utilization data. Generate from known distributions (case durations follow lognormal, volumes follow Poisson). Never use real surgeon names or patient data in dev. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | SageMaker Processing: ~$0.20/hour for ml.m5.xlarge (solve takes 5-30 min quarterly). Lambda: negligible for daily runs. DynamoDB: ~$25/month for on-demand. S3: negligible. QuickSight: $18-24/user/month. Total: $200-800/month depending on user count. |
