[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 235     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Step 2: Demand forecasting.** Before you can optimize block allocations, you need to know how much each service actually needs. Historical volume alone isn't enough because demand changes: new surgeons join, referral patterns shift, service lines expand or contract. A time-series forecast per service gives you expected weekly case volume and total minutes for the upcoming planning period. The forecast includes uncertainty bounds so the optimization can be robust to demand variability. Skip this step and you're allocating based on last year's demand, which may not reflect next quarter's reality.
[0m[49m[39m  236, 252[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  237, 253[0m:[39m[49m ```pseudocode
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 238     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m FUNCTION forecast_demand(raw_case_data, forecast_horizon_weeks):
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 239     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Group historical cases by service and week.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 240     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // We're building a time series: cases per week per service.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 241     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     weekly_volume = GROUP raw_case_data BY (service, iso_week)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 242     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         COMPUTE: case_count, total_minutes, avg_case_duration
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 243     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 244     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // For each service, generate a demand forecast.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 245     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Using a time-series model that captures seasonality, trend, and noise.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 246     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     forecasts = FOR each service:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 247     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         history = weekly_volume filtered to this service
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 248     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         model = fit time-series model (e.g., Prophet, DeepAR, or ARIMA) to history
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 249     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         prediction = model.predict(next forecast_horizon_weeks weeks)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 250     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         // prediction includes: expected_cases, expected_minutes,
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 251     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         //                      lower_bound (10th percentile), upper_bound (90th percentile)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 252     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         RETURN {
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 253     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             service: service,
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 254     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             expected_weekly_minutes: prediction.expected_minutes,
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 255     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             upper_bound_minutes: prediction.upper_bound,  // for robust scheduling
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 256     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             expected_weekly_cases: prediction.expected_cases
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 257     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 258     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 259     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     RETURN forecasts
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION load_constraints(constraint_config):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Parse constraint configuration into solver-ready format.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Each constraint type maps to a specific mathematical inequality or equality.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     room_capabilities = map of room_id -> set of capabilities
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     service_requirements = map of service_id -> required capabilities
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     min_allocations = map of service_id -> minimum blocks per week
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     max_allocations = map of service_id -> maximum blocks per week
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     day_preferences = map of service_id -> list of preferred days
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Validate: every service's required capabilities must exist in at least one room.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // If cardiac needs a bypass machine and no room has one, the problem is infeasible.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR each service in service_requirements:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         compatible_rooms = rooms where capabilities contain all of service.required_capabilities
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF compatible_rooms is empty:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             RAISE error: "Service {service} has no compatible rooms. Check constraint config."
